1. spin up ec2 instance
2. install s3fuse and use that to connect a s3 bucket to instance
3. put UUID folder contents to AWS
4. start a screen session
5. execute command to download file and append `&& touch DOWNLOAD.DONE` (as a done flag upon successful completion)
6. detach the screen
7. document what you've got started with this format:

cat <UUID>.collections.notes
This is the data set that this is collecting:
ftp://<url>

started the job to download: <date>
To reconnect to this job use: screen -R <output of `screen -ls`>

8. have a script running that monitors DOWNLOAD.DONE
9. use aws cli to upload to S3 bucket
10. rinse & repeat
